    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - CAB ACCESSORIES - TROUBLESHOOTING - Electric
        Windshield Washer, With International Turn Signal Switch and Air Wipers
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Electric Windshield Washer, With International Turn Signal Switch and Air Wipers</title>
        <table id="t0823218" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Electric Windshield Washer, With International Turn Signal Switch and Air Wipers</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.85in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.64in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.39in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With ignition key off, check circuit breaker F18 for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>F18</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace circuit breaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Move key switch to ignition position and at F18 and circuit 12B measure voltage to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F18, 12B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 12 or 12B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (457), move key switch to ignition position, and at circuit 82K,
                                measure voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(457), 82K to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 82K, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At conn. (457), measure voltage from circuit 82K to 11-GK.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(457), 82K to 11-GK.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 11-GK, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect windshield washer switch (34) and install jumper wire from circuit 87H to
                                ground. Disconnect conn. (460) and at circuit 87H [going to (34)], measure resistance to
                                gnd.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(460), 87H to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 87H, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (460) and with jumper wire still installed, at conn. (457) circuit
                                87H, measure resistance to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(457), 87H to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 87H, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Test washer switch (34) by measuring resistance across terminals 1 and 2 while switch
                                is on.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Across switch (34) term. 1 and 2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace washer switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (34) and disconnect conn. (460). At (460) measure resistance from
                                circuit 87 to 87H [going to (34)] with washer switch on.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(460), 87 to 87H.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 87, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (460). At (457) measure resistance from circuit 87 to 87H with washer
                                switch on.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(457), 87 to 87H.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 87, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove wash relay (270), move key switch to ignition position, and at cir. 87B measure
                                voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(270), 87B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 87B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At conn. (270) circuit 87E measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(270), 87E to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 87E, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At conn. (457), install jumper wire from circuit 87F to 11-GK, and at conn. (270)
                                circuit 87F measure resistance to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(270), 87F to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 87F, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove jumper wire and reconnect conn. (457). Is washer bottle on left side of
                                vehicle?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 17.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (2) and at relay socket (270), install jumper wire from circuit 87B
                                to 87C. At (2), circuit 87C measure voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(2), 87C to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 87C, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (510) and reconnect conn. (2). At (510) circuit 87B measure voltage
                                to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(510), 87B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 87B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>16.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At conn. (510), measure voltage from circuit 87B to 11-GK.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(510), 87B to 11-GK.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 11-GK, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>17.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>On vehicles with washer bottle on right side of vehicle, disconnect conn. (510) and
                                install a jumper wire from circuit 87B to 87A. At (510) circuit 87A measure voltage to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(510), 87A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 87A, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>18.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At conn. (510) measure voltage from circuit 87A to 87-G.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(510), 87A to 87-G.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 87-G or 11-GE, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>19.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Bench test wash relay (270) by measuring resistance from pin 30 to 87A.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Relay (270), pin 30 to 87A.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace wash relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>20.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Bench test wash relay (270) by applying +12V to pin 86 and ground to 85, and measuring
                                resistance from pin 30 to 87.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Energized relay (270), pin 30 to 87.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace wash relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>21.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With jumper wire still in place at relay socket (270), reconnect conn. (510) and
                                momentarily move key switch to ignition position. Does washer motor run?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace motor.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>22.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove jumper wire and re-install washer relay (270). Move key switch to ignition
                                position and move washer lever to wash position. Does washer function?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Washer cir. check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace wipe/wash module (457).</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
